.simple_container{ :style => 'background-color: #ebebeb;border:none;' }
  .success.summary
    All Ruby developers speak the same language, but all have varying techniques.
    Rewrite the code snippet and provide the best solution. Everyday a new problem
    will be presented, and the best written refactor wins; you decide the winner,
    you provide the solution. Good Luck --
    
  .snippet_container
    #date
      .day= @snippet.displayed_on.strftime('%d')
      .month= @snippet.displayed_on.strftime('%b').upcase!
      .year
        .century 20
        = @snippet.displayed_on.strftime('%y')

    .snippet_nav
      .right_arrow
        %a{ :href => display_snippet_path }
          &nbsp;
      .left_arrow
        %a{ :href => display_snippet_path }
          &nbsp;
      .middle
        SNIPPET OF THE DAY

      
    #snippet.code
      %script{ :type => "text/javascript" } 
        = "document.write('#{@snippet.display}');"
      .hidden=h @snippet.display
      %ul
        %li
          %span.bold Submission by:
          = @snippet.user.login
        %li
          %span.bold Member Since:
          = @snippet.user.created_at.strftime("%b %Y")
        %li
          %span.bold Participation Count:
          = @snippet.user.refactors.count
        %li= link_to "Refactor", "#", :class => 'fork'

      .hidden= render :partial => 'refactors/inline_form', :locals => {:code => @snippet.code}

  = render :partial => 'refactors/refactor', :collection => @snippet.refactors